Cart 353


                                                          Concepts: 50 ideas
                                                          
                                                          
1 - Virtual painting palette to experiment and learn about colors

2 - Different cityscapes with products and services of everyday life, that would inform you of their impacts on (y)our life

3 - Roots: the etymology of words used by young people and found in slangs. Could be done with words found in pop songs for example, 
the song would be playing maybe

4 - A room with basic furniture that you would have to clean regurlarly, and the furnitures would gradually get dirty and would need 
cleaning every week (or every other number of time)

5 - Interactive experience of you selecting drinks (from water to cola to alcohol) and you would see how it alters the visuals on the 
screen (as if it was your eyes)

6 - A soundscape of a place in the city illustrating the amount of noise we are exposed to daily, and you would be able to "clean" the 
sound by removing different elements and modifying parameters (like volume) until optimal sound stimuli

7 - Multiplayer interactive interface where each user writes a number of words (noun, verb, adjective, etc.) and then the interface 
shuffles them according to the category to create phrases.

8 - City landscape where you could switch off the city lights and gradually see the astral spectacle. When switching lights back on, 
you would see less the stars.

9 - Game constituting in guessing what a blurred (or other feature) image is for real

10 - Interactive interface with pictures (one at a time) where you could make appear objects and people when hovering specific locations

11 - An trivial application that would inform you on what corporations omit to tell its citizens and on existing alternatives

12 - Storyline of someone in public transportation; it would be a journey highlighting the surface they enter in contact with (chosen by user) to demonstrate the amount of germs ingested unconsciously in not much time

13 - Soundscape of desktop computer and user complaining on its slow performance; parallel with horse race and commentator 

14 - Landscape of a bedroom with many electronic devices emitting waves, visuals would show how waves are disrupting one's sleep

15 - Puzzle game with photos, with squares getting smaller as leveling up

16 - Pop-up for when you are on facebook, that will remind you everynow and then that you are worthy of love (or other positive things) 
to encourage you to get off your news feed scrolling

17 - Soundscape of someone sextalking to you with a visual of generic body (working as a ruler) and as you move down or up the body with 
the mouse, the sextalk will be focused on that zone of the body

18 - Interface with virtual person conversing with you to learn/improve your spanish

19 - App that would count your time spent on social medias and convert that time into money to finance war in middle east

20 - Game for children to design a prototype of their dream neighborhood (to learn basic design principles)

21 - App that will give you ideas for small rewards when not smoking a cigarette. When drawback, consequences felt on propositions 
(for smokers who want to quit)

22 - Social Network interface for artists to reflect on ideas and collaborate (in real-life or from a distance)

23 - App to signal people in the neighborhood that you have something to give/share/lend (bring back the idea of communicating with 
neighborhood to help each other out)

24 - Interface where you would enter words to organize concepts hierarchically and it would be reorganized in a networked manner

25 - Visual support for timer (e.g. a hourglass), aesthetically beautiful to make the idea of a timer less dry and motivate you to use 
it more often

26 - Archive of ancestral/grand-mother tricks for hygiene and elementary life care, simplified

27 - Digital tool that would increase or decrease screen brightness according to the time of the day, would modulate with cycle of sun

28 - Interactive shower simulation with sounds and visuals of steam and spray of water, meditative

29 - Money-saving program for students, showing amount of money in their pockets when avoiding to buy some stuff, and worthy stuff they 
could afford instead 

30 - Simple mastering template (for sound), to witness how different parameters influence your hearing experience

31 - Game to learn music theory with DNA double helix

32 - Game where you have to write the first word that comes into your mind when seeing a peculiar ad; data from different users then compared

33 - Interactive interface for children where they would feed a living organism with food they like/choose (candy, chips, hot dogs, veggies) 
and the organism would become a scary thing if fed badly 

34 - Digital piggy-bank where you would put money when consciously choosing to not use credit card; after a certain amount, would notify 
your relatives that you deserve a special attention (unrelated to money)

35 - Book with magic spells adapted to modern life

36 - Organizing template to store bills and important documents by scanning and saving in template

37 - Robot that would bring out of the dust old files in your computer you haven't touched in a while and ask you if you still want them. 
Would have an incorporate delete option

38 - Game where you have to rescue the forest by stopping machines from cutting the trees down

39 - Game where you are on a bicycle and you have to avoid holes in the street and getting smashed by cars

40 - Interactive experience of shutting down utilities in the house and/or unplugging them and sound would be modulated by those actions; 
focus brought on white ambient noise we are habituated to

41 - Online painting class for light and shadows

42 - Game where you organize an event and manage potential issues (based on real-life experience)

43 - For kids: Mouth and toothbrush and with mouse you manipulate the toothbrush and alerts will notify you that you have missed areas

44 - Challenge game: Negative words and sentence in negation given and you have to find positive equivalence of the same message

45 - Game where you have to avoid getting hit by coins otherwise you get injured (you lose when you die)

46 - Interface where you train to create good passwords (based on algorithm)

47 - Tool that would change RGB of your screen according on the amount of work you ask to your computer

48 - Interactive interface that would take color from images to create uniform shapes, and you could change size and type of shape 
(and the image itself)

49 - App that records your voicemail and stores them in memory for personal sound database

50 - Animation of cake baking



